Provisional and preliminary results for the Lake Okeechobee 2020/2021 sediment sampling conducted by University of Florida.

Sediment Zones

Sediment zones across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.


* Spatially interpolated using weighted k-nearest neighbor classifier with up to 10 nearest neighbots considered (i.e. k=10; kknn function in the kknn R-library).

Mud Depth

Mud depth across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.


* Spatially interpolated using tension spline (Tps function in the fields R-library).

Bulk Density across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.


* Spatially interpolated using tension spline (Tps function in the fields R-library).

Total Phoshorus

Total phosphorus across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated TP concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

Inorganic Phoshorus (HCl TP)

  • Data was log-transformed prior to variogram fitting.
  • After kriging, the data were back-transformed consistent with Yamamoto (2007) and Journel (1980)

Comparison of original values, back-transformed and corrected back-transformed data.

Inorganic phosphorus (HCl extracted) across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated TP concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

Inorganic Phoshorus (NaHCO3 Pi)

  • Data was log-transformed prior to variogram fitting.
  • After kriging, the data were back-transformed consistent with Yamamoto (2007) and Journel (1980)

Inorganic phosphorus (NaHCO₃ extracted) across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated Pi concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

  • Gaussian model was used to perform kriging.

Inorganic phosphorus (NaHCO₃ extracted) semivariogram comparison.

Inorganic Phoshorus (KCl Pi)

Values below MDL - assumed MDL of 0.17 mg/kg

  • Due to low R2, no kriging was performed (also evaluated data using log-transformed concentrations)

Bubble plot of inorganic phosphorus (KCl extracted) across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including.

Total Nitrogen

  • 69 of the 148 samples were reported less than the MDL (0.200 g kg-1)

Histogram of sediment total nitrogen concentrations sampled across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.

Bubbleplot of total nitrogen across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.

Total Nitrogen across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated Pi concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

  • Spherical model was used to perform kriging.
